632
00:43:32,597 --> 00:43:33,320
Rym: Not everything, though.

633
00:43:33,900 --> 00:43:33,981
Scott: Yeah.

634
00:43:34,001 --> 00:43:36,840
Scott: Like we said, if they're statically loading, it's not an issue, right?

635
00:43:36,900 --> 00:43:41,000
Scott: If they're dynamically loading libraries, then they need to bring those libraries along with them.

636
00:43:41,080 --> 00:43:50,280
Scott: And if there's conflicts, you know, those libraries, different versions of the library have to live alongside each other and load the correct ones, all kinds of things going on there.

637
00:43:51,923 --> 00:43:53,186
