00:50:19,760 --> 00:50:26,220
Scott: I remember with CPAN, they have their own separate package manager for the programming language.

747
00:50:26,862 --> 00:50:27,082
Scott: Right.

748
00:50:27,102 --> 00:50:33,540
Scott: So Python has PyPI, Ruby has Ruby gems, you know, Node JavaScript has NPM.

749
00:50:33,941 --> 00:50:34,062
Scott: Right.

750
00:50:34,082 --> 00:50:35,647
Scott: Which is the worst garbage one.

751
00:50:36,771 --> 00:50:39,180
Scott: It's really poorly managed in general.

752
00:50:40,862 --> 00:50:41,964
Scott: And it's basically so.

753
00:50:42,004 --> 00:50:57,860
Scott: now on top of your operating system package manager, where you're installing software for like the global system, you're also have a separate package manager to install libraries specific to a particular programming language.

754
00:50:59,040 --> 00:51:08,860
Scott: And then on top of that, you have like environment managing things or Docker or containers or whatever you're going to use to when you're working on different projects.

755
00:51:09,361 --> 00:51:09,502
Scott: Right.

756
00:51:09,522 --> 00:51:11,348
Scott: It's like project one install.

