00:52:42,901 --> 00:52:48,676
Scott: But I guess if you want to publish globally, then you do what the person in the news bit did.

790
00:52:48,696 --> 00:52:50,400
Scott: You publish globally, share with the world.

791
00:52:50,960 --> 00:52:54,900
Scott: And then if people start using it and you go ahead and corrupt it, well, they're in trouble.

792
00:52:55,200 --> 00:52:58,411
Rym: But I guess it's similar to what we talked about in the first half of the show.

793
00:52:59,214 --> 00:53:01,020
Rym: This all these different things.

794
00:53:01,280 --> 00:53:06,820
Rym: Installing software on your Windows computer, installing an app on your phone, installing libraries to write code.

795
00:53:07,383 --> 00:53:10,440
Rym: They're all fundamentally the same thing with the same challenges.

796
00:53:11,600 --> 00:53:11,660
Scott: Yep.

797
00:53:11,740 --> 00:53:21,160
Scott: It's basically like these little libraries that have, you know, software and you can you have your programs on your computer that know how to talk to those libraries.

798
00:53:21,761 --> 00:53:27,100
Scott: And the libraries give you instructions on how to get the software and install it onto your computer.

799
00:53:27,461 --> 00:53:28,523
Scott: And you tell the.

800
00:53:28,623 --> 00:53:32,090
Scott: you tell it, hey, this tool, go get this package.

