00:54:47,876 --> 00:54:48,077
Scott: Right.

827
00:54:48,097 --> 00:54:48,397
Scott: Whatever.

828
00:54:48,457 --> 00:54:49,780
Scott: All these it's just a list.

829
00:54:50,000 --> 00:55:04,500
Scott: Basically, it's a JSON file, but it's effectively just a list of all the packages that your program needs to install from somewhere else in order to work, because you're not including that code directly and the versions of each thing that you need.

