882
00:58:40,381 --> 00:58:44,990
Rym: And this is where this is partly like to get to get a little existential and a little roomy about this.

883
00:58:45,390 --> 00:58:50,600
Rym: This is sort of this increasing relaying abstractions upon abstractions upon abstractions.

884
00:58:50,940 --> 00:58:51,742
Rym: And this isn't new.

885
00:58:52,122 --> 00:58:54,465
Rym: Think about that shitty video card we just talked about.

886
00:58:54,866 --> 00:58:56,649
Rym: Computing is all the same fundamental.

887
00:58:56,689 --> 00:58:58,131
Rym: It's all just adders in the end.

888
00:58:58,691 --> 00:59:00,374
Rym: We figured out adders a long time ago.

889
00:59:00,414 --> 00:59:04,760
Rym: We figured out how to add some numbers together with binary logic.

890
00:59:05,200 --> 00:59:07,864
Rym: And we've just been expanding, expanding, expanding upon that.

891
00:59:08,405 --> 00:59:12,772
Rym: And with increased abstraction comes increased specialization.

892
00:59:13,153 --> 00:59:17,500
Rym: Whereas in the old days, a computer scientist wrote code that made the computer go.

893
00:59:17,941 --> 00:59:18,543
Rym: And that was it.

894
00:59:18,924 --> 00:59:24,400
Rym: But look at how many different subspecialties exist to make anything happen in the modern technology world.

895
00:59:26,841 --> 00:59:45,480
